s://rhai.rs/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Rhai</a> script over its JSON input and returns JSON. Scripts are <strong>deterministic and side-effect-free</strong> (no network, no clock, no storage), so they&#39;re safe to retry and easy to test.</p><p>A script body lives in your sync directory as <code>transforms/&lt;name&gt;.rhai</code> and is pushed with <code>primitive sync push</code>:</p><div class="language-"><button title="Copy Code" class="copy"></button><span class="lang"></span><pre class="shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark" style="--shiki-light:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#e1e4e8;--shiki-light-bg:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#24292e;" tabindex="0" dir="ltr"><code><span class="line"><span>// transforms/normalize-order.rhai</span></span>
<span class="line"><span>let items = input.raw.items.filter(|i| i.qty &gt; 0);</span></span>
